{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T8UdeYWzSFyXWGbZbNGtaf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created and verified.\n\n---\n\n**Story created:**\n- **Story ID:** 16.1\n- **Story Key:** 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser\n- **File:** `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser.md`\n- **Status:** ready-for-dev\n\n**What was done:**\n- Auto-discovered story `16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser` as the first backlog story in sprint-status.yaml\n- Analyzed architecture (Decision 4: Hierarchical Flow Model, Decision 5: Engine-Handled Null Tasks), PRD (FR1-FR5, FR18), UX spec, existing schema, and existing parser code\n- Created 11 BDD acceptance criteria covering: schema extension, story_flow/epic_flow parsing, backward compat, hierarchical flow resolution, referential integrity validation, mutual exclusivity of `flow`/`story_flow`, `agent: null` support, and `scope: per-epic` support\n- All 11 ACs tagged `test-provable` -- all can be verified by running tests against the parser/schema without a running app\n- Detailed dev notes with architecture constraints, key interfaces, schema change specifics, backward compat rules, and file references\n- Did NOT update sprint-status.yaml (per instructions)\n- Did NOT commit (per instructions)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- Config file was at `_bmad/config.yaml` not `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` as the workflow.yaml implied. Found it via glob.\n- No `project-context.md` exists in the repo. Skipped that input.\n- The workflow file was `.yaml` not `.md` as the skill loader instruction said (\"LOAD the FULL ... workflow.md\"). Found via glob.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- The epic ACs in `epics-parallel-execution.md` bundled multiple assertions into a single AC block. I decomposed them into 11 separate ACs for testability, adding ACs for edge cases the epic didn't explicitly mention (mutual exclusivity of `flow`/`story_flow`, `agent: null` schema support, `scope: per-epic` enum extension).\n- Added AC #9 (flow/story_flow coexistence rejection) which isn't in the epic but is implied by the architecture doc's statement that `flow:` is \"syntactic sugar for `story_flow:`\" -- they can't both exist.\n- Added AC #10 and #11 for `agent: null` and `scope: per-epic` because the schema must support these for stories 16.2+ to work, and the epic AC explicitly mentions `story_flow` tasks defined in `tasks:` section which implies the agent: null extension must already be in the schema.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- The current schema uses `\"additionalProperties\": false` at top level. Adding `execution`, `story_flow`, `epic_flow` requires either removing that constraint or listing all new keys. This is straightforward but must be done carefully to avoid breaking existing validation.\n- The `oneOf` approach for allowing either `flow` or `story_flow` at the JSON Schema level can be complex with Ajv. May be simpler to make both optional in the schema and enforce mutual exclusivity in TypeScript code.\n\n**Observations:**\n- This is the first story in a new epic (16) and the first story in the parallel execution feature set. No previous story in this epic to draw learnings from.\n- The existing `workflow-parser.ts` is well-structured with a clear `validateAndResolve` pipeline, making integration straightforward.\n- All ACs are `test-provable` since this story is purely schema+parser work with no runtime behavior to observe.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 23\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 10, Glob: 7, Write: 1, Edit: 0, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `ls tests/` (~28 lines), `ls src/lib/__tests__/ | tail` (~26 lines), `git log --oneline -10` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 12 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None significant. The glob for `_bmad/**/config.yaml` could have been avoided if th