{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EbWLuRzBfXxKEeXQE4hLnQ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"4691 passed, 1 failed (pre-existing `stats.test.ts`). No regressions from the review fixes.\n\n---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser.md\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0 (File List matches git changes)\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 7 Medium, 2 Low\n\n## HIGH Issues (Fixed)\n\n1. **`hierarchical-flow.ts` — No input validation on execution config fields or flow array structure.** The `resolveHierarchicalFlow` function is a public export that accepts `Record<string, unknown>` but performed no runtime validation, blindly casting values. Invalid types (e.g., `max_parallel: \"many\"`, `loop: 42`) would silently produce malformed objects. **Fixed:** Added `resolveExecutionConfig()` with field-level validation and `normalizeFlowArray()` with structural validation. Added 13 new tests.\n\n## MEDIUM Issues (Fixed)\n\n2. **`hierarchical-flow.ts` — Unsafe `as LoopBlock` cast** (lines 74-75, 80-81). **Fixed:** `normalizeFlowArray()` now validates loop block structure before casting.\n\n3. **`workflow-parser.ts` line 191 — Operator precedence issue** with `as` cast and `??`. **Fixed:** Replaced with explicit type annotation.\n\n4. **`run.ts` line 141 — Incomplete null guard** on `task.agent`. Used `!== null` instead of `!= null`, wouldn't catch `undefined`. **Fixed:** Changed to `!= null`.\n\n5. **Missing test — `story_flow` loop blocks referencing undefined task.** **Fixed:** Added test case.\n\n6. **Missing test — `epic_flow` loop blocks referencing undefined non-built-in task.** **Fixed:** Added test case.\n\n7. **Missing test — `epic_strategy` validation error path.** **Fixed:** Added test case.\n\n8. **Missing test — `story_strategy` validation error path.** **Fixed:** Added test case.\n\n## LOW Issues (Not Fixed)\n\n9. **Duplicate coexistence check** — `flow`/`story_flow` coexistence is validated in both `resolveHierarchicalFlow()` and `validateAndResolve()`. The check in `hierarchical-flow.ts` is dead code when called through the parser. Kept for defense-in-depth as a public API safety net.\n\n10. **`resolveHierarchicalFlow` silently accepts no flow** — When neither `flow` nor `story_flow` is present, returns empty `storyFlow`. Not dangerous since the parser catches this upstream, but the public API is permissive.\n\n**Review Complete**\n\n- **Story Status:** verifying\n- **Issues Fixed:** 8 (1 HIGH, 7 MEDIUM)\n- **Tests:** 28 -> 43 (+15 new tests)\n- **Coverage:** hierarchical-flow.ts 100%, workflow-parser.ts 90.5%, schema-validate.ts 100%\n\nFiles modified:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` — Added input validation, `resolveExecutionConfig()`, `normalizeFlowArray()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — Fixed operator precedence\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` — Fixed null guard\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/hierarchical-flow.test.ts` — Added 15 tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser.md` — Status -> verifying\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `resolveHierarchicalFlow` accepted arbitrary types without validation, producing silently malformed `ExecutionConfig` and `FlowStep[]` objects. Could cause runtime crashes downstream.\n- MEDIUM: Operator precedence issue in `workflow-parser.ts` with `as` cast + `??` (worked by accident).\n- MEDIUM: `run.ts` null guard used `!== null` instead of `!= null`, wouldn't catch `undefined` agent values.\n\n**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Duplicate `flow`/`story_flow` coexistence check in two files (defense-in-depth, acceptable).\n- `resolveHierarchicalFlow` silently returns empty `storyFlow` when no flow is provided (upstream parser catches this).\n\n**Coverag