{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AsqLvhcvTpwtSdJRys1tjW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# src/commands/\n2\t\n3\tCLI command implementations for the `codeharness` tool. Each file exports a `register*Command(program)` function that adds a command (or command group) to the Commander program instance. All commands are registered in `src/index.ts`.\n4\t\n5\t## Commands\n6\t\n7\t### init.ts\n8\tInitializes the harness in a project. Detects stack (Node.js/Python) and app type, installs dependencies, sets up Beads issue tracking, installs BMAD with patches, creates state file, scaffolds AGENTS.md and docs/, instruments OTLP, and starts the Docker observability stack.\n9\t- **Key deps:** `lib/stack-detect`, `lib/state`, `lib/deps`, `lib/beads`, `lib/bmad`, `lib/otlp`, `lib/docker`, `lib/templates`, `lib/stack-path`\n10\t- **Subcommands:** none (single action)\n11\t\n12\t### bridge.ts\n13\tBridges BMAD epics/stories into the Beads task store. Parses a BMAD epics markdown file, extracts stories with acceptance criteria, and imports them as Beads issues with deduplication.\n14\t- **Key deps:** `lib/bmad` (parser), `lib/beads` (issue creation), `lib/output`\n15\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epics <path>`, supports `--dry-run`\n16\t\n17\t### run.ts\n18\tExecutes the autonomous coding loop. Pre-flight checks: plugin directory, state reconciliation, Docker availability (`isDockerAvailable()`), and orphan container cleanup (`cleanupContainers()`). Then reads sprint status, generates Ralph prompt, and spawns the agent driver with configurable iteration limits, timeouts, and retry counts. Pipes agent stdout/stderr through `driver.parseOutput()` into the Ink renderer.\n19\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (isDockerAvailable), `modules/infra` (cleanupContainers), `modules/sprint` (readSprintStatusFromState, reconcileState, getSprintState), `lib/agents` (getDriver), `lib/ink-renderer` (startRenderer), `lib/output`\n20\t- **Exports:** `resolvePluginDir()`, `countStories` (re-export from run-helpers), `registerRunCommand(program)`\n21\t- **Subcommands:** none (single action with many options)\n22\t\n23\t### verify.ts\n24\tRuns the verification pipeline on completed work. Two modes: (1) story verification via `--story <id>` — parses acceptance criteria, checks preconditions, validates proof quality (rejects proofs with PENDING ACs), creates proof document, runs Showboat verify, updates state, closes Beads issue, moves exec-plan to completed; (2) retrospective verification via `--retro --epic <n>` — checks that `epic-N-retrospective.md` exists, marks it done in sprint-status.yaml. JSON output includes `proofQuality` metrics.\n25\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (parseStoryACs, validateProofQuality, checkPreconditions, etc.), `lib/doc-health` (exec-plan completion), `lib/beads-sync` (sprint status for retro)\n26\t- **Flags:** `--story <id>` (story mode), `--retro` + `--epic <n>` (retro mode), `--json`\n27\t\n28\t### status.ts\n29\tDisplays current harness status and health. Shows version, stack, enforcement settings, Docker/observability state (mode-aware: local-shared, remote-direct, remote-routed), Beads summary, onboarding progress, session flags, coverage, and verification log. Supports `--check` for pass/fail health checks.\n30\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker`, `lib/state`, `lib/beads`, `lib/onboard-checks`, `lib/stack-path`\n31\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-docker`, `--check`\n32\t\n33\t### onboard.ts\n34\tAlias for `audit` (FR16). Delegates all behavior to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler, ensuring identical output. Provides a deprecated `scan` subcommand that prints a warning before running audit.\n35\t- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit), `lib/output` (warn)\n36\t- **Exports:** `registerOnboardCommand(program)`\n37\t- **Subcommands:** `scan` (deprecated, prints warning then runs audit)\n38\t\n39\t### audit-action.ts\n40\tShared audit action handler used by both `audit.ts` and `onboard.ts`. Contains the full audit execution logic: precondition checks, `runAudit()`, `--fix` handling (generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), and output formatting (human and JSON).\n41\t- **Key deps:** `modules/audit` (runAudit, generateFixStories, addFixStoriesToState), `modules/audit/report` (formatAuditHuman, formatAuditJson), `lib/onboard-checks` (runPreconditions), `lib/output`\n42\t- **Exports:** `executeAudit(opts: { isJson: boolean; isFix: boolean })`\n43\t\n44\t### teardown.ts\n45\tRemoves the harness from a project. Stops Docker containers (mode-aware), cleans OTLP instrumented scripts from package.json, deletes state file and .harness/ cache. Preserves _bmad/ and docs/ by default.\n46\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state`, `lib/observability`, `lib/docker`, `lib/stack-path`\n47\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--keep-docker`\n48\t\n49\t### state.ts\n50\tManages harness state via subcommands. Provides read/write access to the YAML frontmatter state file using dot-notation keys.\n51\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (read/write/get/set), `yaml` (stringify for display)\n52\t- **Subcommands:** `show`, `get <key>`, `set <key> <value>`, `reset-session`\n53\t\n54\t### sync.ts\n55\tSynchronizes Beads issue statuses with story files and sprint-status.yaml. Supports bidirectional, beads-to-files, and files-to-beads directions. Can sync a single story or all stories.\n56\t- **Key deps:** `lib/beads` (issue CRUD), `lib/beads-sync` (sync logic)\n57\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--direction <dir>`, `--story <key>`\n58\t\n59\t### coverage.ts\n60\tRuns tests with coverage measurement and evaluates results against targets. Detects the coverage tool (c8/coverage.py), runs or checks coverage, evaluates against project target, checks per-file coverage floors, and updates state.\n61\t- **Key deps:** `lib/coverage` (detection, execution, evaluation)\n62\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--check-only`, `--story <id>`, `--min-file <percent>`\n63\t\n64\t### doc-health.ts\n65\tScans documentation for freshness and quality issues. Checks whether AGENTS.md files and other docs are stale relative to their associated source code. Can scope checks to modules changed by a specific story.\n66\t- **Key deps:** `lib/doc-health` (scanning, freshness checks)\n67\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <id>`, `--fix` (placeholder)\n68\t\n69\t### stack.ts\n70\tManages the shared observability stack (Docker-based). Starts, stops, and shows status of the VictoriaMetrics/OTel Collector stack. Mode-aware: handles local-shared, remote-direct, and remote-routed configurations.\n71\t- **Key deps:** `lib/docker` (stack lifecycle), `lib/state`, `lib/stack-path`\n72\t- **Subcommands:** `start`, `stop`, `status`\n73\t\n74\t### retro-import.ts\n75\tImports retrospective action items as beads issues. Parses `epic-N-retrospective.md` for action item tables, classifies each item (harness/tool/project), derives priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids.\n76\t- **Key deps:** `lib/retro-parser` (parsing, classification, priority), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n77\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--epic <n>`, supports `--json`\n78\t\n79\t### github-import.ts\n80\tImports GitHub issues labeled for sprint planning into beads. Queries GitHub via `gh` CLI for issues with a specified label (default: `sprint-candidate`), maps GitHub labels to beads type (bug/story/task) and priority, creates or deduplicates beads issues using gap-ids with format `[source:github:owner/repo#N]`.\n81\t- **Key deps:** `lib/github` (isGhAvailable, ghIssueSearch, getRepoFromRemote), `lib/beads` (createOrFindIssue, buildGapId), `lib/output`\n82\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--repo <owner/repo>`, `--label <label>`, `--json`\n83\t\n84\t### retry.ts\n85\tManages retry state for stories. Shows retry counts and flagged-story status, resets counters per-story or globally. Validates story keys against path traversal.\n86\t- **Key deps:** `lib/retry-state` (readRetries, readFlaggedStories, resetRetry), `lib/output`\n87\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--reset`, `--story <key>`, `--status`, `--json`\n88\t\n89\t### validate.ts\n90\tParent command for the `codeharness validate` group. Registers subcommands `schema` (from `validate-schema.ts`) and `self` (from `validate-self.ts`).\n91\t- **Key deps:** `validate-schema` (registerValidateSchemaCommand), `validate-self` (registerValidateSelfCommand)\n92\t- **Subcommands:** `schema` (validate YAML against JSON schemas), `self` (self-validation cycle)\n93\t\n94\t### validate-schema.ts\n95\tCLI subcommand: `codeharness validate schema`. Validates workflow YAML files against JSON schemas using `parseWorkflow()`. Accepts a path or directory, validates each `.yaml`/`.yml` file, and reports results.\n96\t- **Key deps:** `lib/workflow-parser` (parseWorkflow, WorkflowParseError), `lib/output`\n97\t- **Exports:** `registerValidateSchemaCommand(parent)`\n98\t\n99\t### validate-self.ts\n100\tCLI subcommand: `codeharness validate self`. Runs self-validation cycle and produces a release gate report. Initializes a validation sprint, loops through `runValidationCycle()` until no actionable ACs remain, then outputs a summary. Outputs \"RELEASE GATE: PASS -- v1.0 ready\" when all non-blocked ACs pass.\n101\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (createValidationSprint, runValidationCycle, getValidationProgress, getACById), `lib/output`\n102\t- **Exports:** `registerValidateSelfCommand(parent)`\n103\t\n104\t### validate-state.ts\n105\tValidates sprint-state.json consistency against sprint-status.yaml. Thin CLI wrapper that delegates to the sprint module's `validateStateConsistency`.\n106\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (validateStateConsistency), `lib/output`\n107\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--state <path>`, `--sprint-status <path>`\n108\t\n109\t### timeout-report.ts\n110\tCaptures diagnostic data from a timed-out iteration. Called by ralph.sh on exit code 124 to preserve git diff, state delta, and partial stderr in a structured markdown report.\n111\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (captureTimeoutReport), `lib/output`\n112\t- **Subcommands:** none; requires `--story <key>`, `--iteration <n>`, `--duration <minutes>`, `--output-file <path>`, `--state-snapshot <path>`; supports `--json`\n113\t\n114\t### query.ts\n115\tQueries observability data (logs, metrics, traces) scoped to the current project. Automatically injects service_name filtering into LogsQL and PromQL queries. Resolves endpoints from state (local or remote).\n116\t- **Key deps:** `lib/state` (service name, endpoint resolution)\n117\t- **Subcommands:** `logs <filter>`, `metrics <promql>`, `traces`\n118\t\n119\t### progress.ts\n120\tUpdates live run progress in sprint-state.json. Used by harness-run to show real-time story/phase progress during autonomous execution.\n121\t- **Key deps:** `modules/sprint` (updateRunProgress, clearRunProgress), `lib/output`\n122\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--story <key>`, `--phase <phase>`, `--action <text>`, `--ac-progress <text>`, `--clear`, `--json`\n123\t\n124\t### observability-gate.ts\n125\tChecks observability coverage against targets for commit gating. Reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against configurable targets (default: 80% static, 60% runtime). Used by the pre-commit hook to block commits below target.\n126\t- **Key deps:** `modules/observability` (checkObservabilityCoverageGate), `lib/output`\n127\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--min-static <percent>`, `--min-runtime <percent>`\n128\t\n129\t### audit.ts\n130\tThin CLI wrapper that registers the `audit` command and delegates to the shared `audit-action.ts` handler. Supports `--json` and `--fix` flags.\n131\t- **Key deps:** `audit-action` (executeAudit)\n132\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--json`, `--fix`\n133\t\n134\t### stats.ts\n135\tAnalyzes token consumption and cost from ralph session logs. Parses JSONL log files for streaming API events, aggregates by phase (create-story, dev-story, code-review, verify, retro), story, tool, and date. Computes API-equivalent cost using Opus 4.6 pricing. Formats human-readable markdown report.\n136\t- **Key deps:** `lib/output` (info, ok, fail, jsonOutput), node:fs, commander\n137\t- **Subcommands:** none; supports `--save` (write report to cost-report.md), `--json`\n138\t\n139\t### verify-env.ts\n140\tManages the verification environment for black-box story verification. Builds a Docker image from project artifacts (no source code), prepares clean temp workspaces with only story docs, validates the environment, and cleans up.\n141\t- **Key deps:** `modules/verify` (buildVerifyImage, prepareVerifyWorkspace, checkVerifyEnv, cleanupVerifyEnv), `lib/output`\n142\t- **Subcommands:** `build` (build Docker image, supports `--json`), `prepare --story <key>` (create clean workspace), `check` (validate image/CLI/otel), `cleanup --story <key>` (remove workspace and container)\n143\t\n144\t### issue.ts\n145\tManages lightweight file-based issue tracking via `.codeharness/issues.yaml`. Supports creating, listing, and closing issues with auto-generated sequential IDs (`issue-NNN`).\n146\t- **Key deps:** `lib/issue-tracker` (createIssue, closeIssue, readIssues), `lib/output`\n147\t- **Exports:** `registerIssueCommand(program)`\n148\t- **Subcommands:** `create <title>` (with `--priority`, `--source`), `list` (with `--json`), `close <id>`\n149\t\n150\t## Adding a New Command\n151\t\n152\t1. Create `src/commands/<name>.ts` exporting `register<Name>Command(program: Command): void`\n153\t2. Register in `src/index.ts`, add tests in `src/commands/__tests__/`\n154\t3. Support `--json` output via `cmd.optsWithGlobals().json` and `jsonOutput()` from `lib/output`\n155\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0116174wQNpVuEKBqTmHzsQd","session_id":"9c9fe147-c536-4d36-9f64-8249f0c68839","uuid":"babfce8b-9df0-4cb2-9a4a-4083da559c74","timestamp":"2026-04-03T17:02:52.537Z"}
