{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RpMoikKpUqiHFF1yR6jAc6","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verification Proof: 16-1 Hierarchical Flow Schema & Parser\n2\t\n3\tStory: `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-1-hierarchical-flow-schema-parser.md`\n4\tVerified: 2026-04-03\n5\tTier: test-provable\n6\tMethod: local CLI checks (build, test, lint, coverage, file inspection)\n7\t\n8\t## Pre-flight Checks\n9\t\n10\t| Check | Result | Detail |\n11\t|-------|--------|--------|\n12\t| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS | tsup compiled successfully, no errors |\n13\t| Tests (`npx vitest run`) | PASS (4691/4692) | 1 pre-existing failure in `stats.test.ts` (unrelated to story) |\n14\t| Lint (`npm run lint`) | WARN | 1 error + 52 warnings — all pre-existing, none in story files |\n15\t| Coverage (`hierarchical-flow.ts`) | 100% Stmts, 100% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines | Full coverage on new file |\n16\t\n17\t## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n18\t\n19\t## AC 1: `execution` object in schema with correct properties and defaults\n20\t<!-- verification: test-provable -->\n21\t\n22\t**Result: PASS**\n23\t\n24\t- **File existence:** `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` exists (5004 bytes)\n25\t- **Schema evidence:** Schema defines `execution` object with properties `max_parallel` (integer, default 1), `isolation` (enum worktree|none, default none), `merge_strategy` (enum rebase|merge-commit, default merge-commit), `epic_strategy` (enum parallel|sequential, default sequential), `story_strategy` (enum sequential|parallel, default sequential)\n26\t- **Test evidence:** 5 tests pass:\n27\t  - `accepts a valid execution section with all properties`\n28\t  - `accepts execution with partial properties (defaults apply)`\n29\t  - `accepts empty execution object`\n30\t  - `rejects invalid isolation value`\n31\t  - `rejects invalid epic_strategy value`\n32\t  - `applies default execution values when execution section absent`\n33\t\n34\t## AC 2: `story_flow`